Oversized rear spinner wheels easily glide over rough terrain
Smaller, recessed front wheels increase interior packing space

body.description: Sleek, spacious, and built to last, the Thule Subterra Carry On Spinner is designed to help you pack and travel efficiently. This carry on spinner guarantees a smooth pull from doorstep to destination thanks to the exclusive 8-wheel system featuring oversized rear wheels that glide over any terrain, and smaller, recessed front wheels that help maximize packing space. Perfect for business travel or a family vacation, the Thule Subterra Carry On comes equipped with an internal compression board to maximize packing space, minimize wrinkling, and keep clothes in place. The divided main compartment also separates clean-from-dirty and work-from-play, so you are sure to stay organized wherever you go. All Thule rolling luggage is constructed to withstand the rigors of modern travel, and this travel bag is no exception. Durable materials, a solid exoskeleton and a molded back panel combine to absorb impact and leave you with a suitcase always ready for the next adventure. Sit back, relax, and enjoy the journey.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 17, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Handle broke after 4 months of use and Thule replaced with lifetime warranty
reviews.reviewText: I travel often and bought this bag for the spinner function and it looked nice. I travel often and after 4 months of use, the handle snapped off. I contacted the Thule to process the lifetime warranty. I submitted the form online with proof of purchase and photo and was told I would be contacted within 48 hours. I followed up again later in the week after but hearing anything or receiving an email. It has now been a week and I have not heard back from the company. I will follow up again next week and provide an update.Update: Thule did process their lifetime warranty with proof of purchase and photos of the bag. They also shipped the bag to me without having to ship the broken bag back. However, you have to be vigilant in following up with the company as it did take over a week of calling consistently to get them to process the claim.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 6, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love this great little carry-on!
reviews.reviewText: No one will challenge you for trying to carry this Thule rolling bag onto a plane or train. It’s truly the correct size for carry-on. That means it’s small. I can pack enough for a 3-5 day trip, if I also carry on a small backpack. But that’s the limit. Of course you can use it to complement a checked bag for longer trips.There is no chemical smell inside the bag, and no warning about harmful chemicals. This is important to me. I feel safe putting my clothes into this bag.The four wheels make the bag incredibly maneuverable. And the compartments help keep me organized. I don’t use the compression thing, because I can fit in a lot of stuff without it.
